```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 9, 38, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916215318, 'comment_body': 'A lot of the child HTML components seem to be the same and so it will be difficult to make changes in the future—you'd have to check each "version", compare the diff and make changes in each version. Is it possible to extract the common parts into subcomponents?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 19, 29, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sagangwee', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916218057, 'comment_body': 'The `wrapTextWithEllipsis` might need to be dynamically adjusted based on the breakpoint, since it looks like the text is truncated too early when breakpoint < 500px.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 19, 33, 46, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sagangwee', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916218543, 'comment_body': 'Where does this number come from? Would be good to document in a comment.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 19, 34, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sagangwee', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916221935, 'comment_body': 'Could we use a template literal for this to avoid the String cast?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 19, 39, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sagangwee', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916224362, 'comment_body': "Will this only be relevant only for opportunities-list-item.component.html? If so, then let's update the constant name to reflect that, since currently it makes it sound like the breakpoint value is relevant for the entire contributor dashboard, which I don't think it is (e.g. I remember there being many different breakpoint values in the last PR).", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 7, 19, 42, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sagangwee', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 916958551, 'commen